<TITLE> Govt to parole Khaleda, sons Saturday: lawyer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com)  The government will parole former prime minister Khaleda Zia along with her two sons Saturday to allow them to attend the funeral of her mother who died in Dinajpur late Friday, a lawyer said. Barrister Ahmed Azam Khan told bdnews24.com at 11:45pm Friday that the body of Toyeba Majumdar would be flown to Dhaka Cantonment. Toyeba's son Shamim Eskanderaccompanied by his wifearrived in Dinajpur Saturday morning to take the dead body to Dhaka. "The body would be kept at [Khaleda's] cantonment home," Azam said. On when the body would be taken to Dhaka, the lawyer said: "I don't think it would happen at night. There is a strong possibility that the body would be brought tomorrow (Saturday) morning." It was not clear if the government would release them together. The lawyer said they had asked authorities to allow the three to see the body together. Toyeba died of heart attack Friday at a Dinajpur hospital aged 87, a doctor said. Doctors at Zia Heart Foundation and Research Institute in Dinajpur declared her dead at 8:45pm after she was taken to the hospital from her home in the town, according to Dr Mosaddek. She suddenly felt pain in her chest at 8:30pm at her Balubari home in the town. Azam had earlier told bdnews24.com by phone that he had asked the home adviser to free them on parole. The lawyer said he talked to MA Matin at 10:30pm. "I have requested him (Matin) to allow them to go to Dinajpur," he said. "The adviser told me that he would let me know after talking to the chief adviser," Azam told bdnews24.com by phone at 11pm. "We're waiting for the phone call of the home adviser," Azam had said. Earlier, reached by phone, home secretary Abdul Karim would not elaborate on the matter. "We are working on that," he said. Deputy inspector general, prisons, Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com by phone that he and Inspector general (prisons) Brigadier General Zakir Hasan broke the news to Khaleda at 10:40pm at the special jail in the Jatiya Sangsad Bhaban complex. The former prime minister has been detained there since Sept 3 last year, pending trial. The sons have been detained in Dhaka Central Jail. He said he had informed Tarique Rahman and Arafat Rahman Coco about the death at 10:15pm. bdnews24.com Dinajpur correspondent said the body was taken home at 9:10pm. Senior BNP leaders including M Saifur Rahman, Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan and Khandaker Delwar Hossain condoled the death. bdnews24.com/c
